partial protection feature.",pr_snowball_about_text_whats_snowball_two="Choose Bullish Snowball if you expect prices to trade within a certain range or go up moderately.",pr_snowball_about_text_whats_snowball_three="Choose Bearish Snowball if you expect prices to trade within a certain range or go down moderately.",pr_snowball_about_text_whats_snowball_four="The settlement amount is determined based on whether knock-out and knock-in events occur.",pr_snowball_about_title_key_product_terms="Key product terms",pr_snowball_about_title_knockout_event="Knock-out event",pr_snowball_about_text_knockout_event_one="A knock-out event occurs when the crypto price is equal to or crosses the knock-out price level. Knock-out events are observed every Friday, 08:00 UTC only.",pr_snowball_about_text_knockout_event_two="If the crypto price reaches the knock-out price at any other day or time, it won't qualify as a knock-out event. A knock-out event occurring is positive because you'll earn interest.",pr_snowball_about_title_knockin_event="Knock-in event",pr_snowball_about_text_knockin_event_one="A knock-in event is said to have occurred when the price of the crypto is equal to or crosses the knock-in price level. Knock-in events are observed every day 08:00 UTC only.",pr_snowball_about_text_knockin_event_two="If the crypto price reaches the knock-in price at any other time, it won't qualify as a knock-in event. A knock-in event is negative because your principal will be exchanged for the alternative crypto and at a worse rate.",pr_snowball_about_title_intro_strike_price="Strike price",pr_snowball_about_text_intro_strike_price="The strike price is the agreed crypto price during the subscription period.",pr_snowball_about_title_knockout_price="Knock-out price",pr_snowball_about_text_knockout_price="The knock-out price is a predetermined price set much closer to the strike price than the knock-in price.",pr_snowball_about_title_knockin_price="Knock-in price",pr_snowball_about_text_knockin_price="The knock-in price is a predetermined price that's set much further away from the strike price than the knock-out price.",pr_snowball_about_text_intro_price_barriers_five="A KI event can occur every day, but only at 08:00 UTC. If the crypto price reaches the KI price at any other time, it won't qualify as a KI event.",pr_snowball_about_title_how_prices_determined="How is the crypto price for knock-out, knock-in and expiration events determined?",pr_snowball_about_text_how_prices_determined="The knock-out price, knock-in price, and expiration price are determined by the average index price of the underlying crypto between 07:00 ～ 08:00 UTC on their respective dates.",pr_snowball_about_title_return_scenarios="Return scenarios",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_positive="{positive} Either a knock-out event takes place, or the product expires without a knock-in event occurring.",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_positive_variable="Positive:",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_neutral="{neutral} A knock-in event occurs but the crypto price expires between the knock-out price and the strike price.",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_neutral_variable="Neutral:",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_negative="{negative} A knock-in event occurs and your expiration price is below the strike price for Bullish Snowball and above the strike price for Bearish Snowball. Your principal will be exchanged for the alternative crypto and at a worse rate.",pr_snowball_about_text_return_scenarios_negative_variable="Negative (currency exchange):",pr_snowball_about_title_getting_started="Getting started",pr_snowball_about_text_getting_started_zero="Ensure you have at least {amountThree} BTC, {amountOne} USDT, or {amountTwo} ETH in your account and get in touch with our sales team.",pr_snowball_about_text_getting_started_one="Pick between the Bullish and Bearish strategies. For Bullish strategies, you must deposit USDT. For Bearish strategies, you must deposit BTC or ETH.",pr_snowball_about_text_getting_started_two="Choose your investment amount and term length.",pr_snowball_about_text_principal_protected_one="No, Snowball isn't a principal protected product. However, there is partial protection until the crypto price crosses your knock-in price.",pr_snowball_about_title_is_principal_protected="Is Snowball a principal protected product?",pr_snowball_about_text_incur_losses="Yes, it's possible to incur losses in scenarios where your crypto hits the KI price. Go to the question: 'How are my earnings calculated?' to learn more about how you may incur a loss.",pr_snowball_about_title_incur_losses="Can I incur losses in Snowball?",pr_snowball_about_text_term_determined="If a knock-out takes place before the expiration date, the term length will be reduced to the number of days the order remained open. The term length remains its original length as long as a knock-out doesn't take place or a knock-out takes place on the expiration date.",pr_snowball_about_title_term_determined="How is the Term determined?",pr_snowball_about_title_earnings_calculated="How are my earnings calculated?",pr_snowball_about_text_how_often_observed="Knock-out events are only observed every Friday and are determined by the average index price of the underlying crypto between 07:00 UTC ～ 08:00 UTC. If crypto price reaches the knock-out price at any other day or time, it won't qualify as a knock-out event. Knock-in events are observed daily, 08:00 UTC and are determined by the average index price of the underlying crypto between 07:00 UTC ～ 08:00 UTC. If the crypto price reaches the knock-in price at any other time, it won't qualify as a knock-in event.",pr_snowball_about_text_ko_after_ki="What happens if I knock-out after a knock-in?",pr_snowball_about_text_when_receive_earnings="On the expiration date, your earnings will be calculated at around 08:00 UTC and will be credited to your Funding account at around 10:00 UTC. If a KO event occurs, your earnings will be calculated and credited to your Funding account on the KO date.",pr_snowball_about_title_when_receive_earnings="When will I receive my earnings?",pr_snowball_about_text_early_redemption="No, you won't be able to apply for early redemption. However, Snowball products may expire early if a knock-out event occurs before the expiration date.",pr_snowball_about_title_early_redemption="Can I apply for early redemption?",pr_snowball_about_text_earnings_calculated_bullish="Bullish",pr_snowball_about_text_earnings_calculated_bearish="Bearish",pr_snowball_about_subtitle_earn_interest="Earn interest",pr_snowball_about_text_ko_occurs_2="{note} You'll still receive interest on the KO date even if a KI event occurs.",pr_snowball_about_text_note="Note:",pr_snowball_about_text_no_ko_ki="No KO or KI event occurs:",pr_snowball_about_text_ko_occurs_1="A KO event occurs:",pr_snowball_about_text_principal_note="Principal x (1 + APR x Term / 365)",pr_snowball_about_subtitle_neutral="Neutral",pr_snowball_about_text_ki_event="KI event occurs and the crypto price is between the strike price and KO price on the expiration date:",pr_snowball_about_text_neutral="You'll receive your principal with no loss or gain",pr_snowball_about_subtitle_incur_losses="Currency exchange — incur losses",pr_snowball_about_text_incur_losses_one="KI event occurs and the crypto price on the expiration date is:",pr_snowball_about_text_incur_losses_two="At or below the strike price: Principal / Strike price",pr_snowball_about_text_incur_losses_three="At or above the strike price: Principal x Strike price"}
